IMPORTANT NOTICES:

1. CUSTODIAL ESCROW DISCLAIMER:
   This software includes a custodial escrow system that generates and manages
   cryptographic keys. The operators of this software have a fiduciary duty to
   protect user funds. Use at your own risk.

2. SECURITY:
   While this software implements industry-standard security practices including
   AES-256-CBC encryption, no system is completely secure. Users and operators
   should:
   - Perform thorough security audits before production use
   - Implement additional security measures as needed
   - Maintain proper insurance coverage
   - Follow all applicable regulations

3. REGULATORY COMPLIANCE:
   Custodial escrow services may be subject to financial regulations in your
   jurisdiction. Users and operators are solely responsible for ensuring
   compliance with all applicable laws, including but not limited to:
   - Money Service Business (MSB) requirements
   - Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations
   - Anti-Money Laundering (AML) requirements
   - Securities laws
   - Consumer protection laws

4. NO WARRANTY:
   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. The authors
   and copyright holders shall not be liable for any damages, including loss
   of funds, arising from the use of this software.

5. ENCRYPTION KEY MANAGEMENT:
   The security of the custodial system depends entirely on proper encryption
   key management. Users and operators are responsible for:
   - Generating secure encryption keys
   - Storing keys in secure secret management systems
   - Implementing proper key rotation procedures
   - Maintaining backup and recovery procedures

6. AUDIT RECOMMENDATION:
   Before deploying this software in a production environment with real funds,
   it is strongly recommended to:
   - Conduct a third-party security audit
   - Perform penetration testing
   - Review all code and configuration
   - Test extensively on testnets
   - Implement comprehensive monitoring

7. UPDATES AND MAINTENANCE:
   Users and operators are responsible for:
   - Keeping dependencies up to date
   - Monitoring security advisories
   - Applying patches promptly
   - Maintaining secure infrastructure

